{{Infobox Japanese deity | Name = Kushiyatama | Deity Type =<!-- Heavenly deity, earthly deity, etc. --> | Full Name = Kushiyatama no Kami (櫛八玉神) | Other Names = Kushiyatama no Mikoto, Kiyahatama no Kami, Kiyahatama no Mikoto | Divine Role = {{ill|God of Cuisine|ja|料理神|12=draft}}, {{ill|God of Cormorants|ja|鵜の神|12=draft}} | Ancestry = * Grandfather: {{ill|Hayakitsuhiko no Kami|ja|速秋津日子神|12=draft}} (Water God) * Grandmother: {{ill|Hayakitsuhime no Kami|ja|速秋津比売神|12=draft}} (Water Goddess) | Shrines = * Mikado-nushi-hiko Shrine * Hida Takatsue Shrine * Kiyahatama Shrine * {{ill|Wadatsumi Shrine|ja|和田津見神社|12=draft}} * {{ill|Minato Shrine (Izumo-taisha)|ja|湊社|12=draft}} * Kashima Shrine (Zōfu Shrine) * {{ill|Homori Shrine|ja|火守神社|12=draft}} * Kushiyatama Shrine | Related Clans = Bekke clan | Texts = {{ill|Kojiki|ja|古事記|12=draft}} }}
'''Kushiyatama''' (櫛八玉神), also known as Kiyahatama no Kami, is a deity appearing in {{ill|Japanese mythology|ja|日本神話|12=draft}}.
== Overview == Kushiyatama appears in the {{ill|Kojiki|ja|古事記|12=draft}} during the episode of the {{ill|Transfer of the Land|ja|国譲り|12=draft}}. He is considered the ancestor of the Bekke clan.
== Depiction == === In the Kojiki === After {{ill|Takeminakata|ja|建御名方神|12=draft}} surrenders to {{ill|Takemikazuchi|ja|建御雷神|12=draft}}, Takemikazuchi asks {{ill|Ōkuninushi|ja|大国主神|12=draft}} about his loyalty. Ōkuninushi agrees to submit the land of Ashihara-no-Nakatsukuni if a grand palace is built for him, akin to the residence of the heavenly gods.
During the construction of the heavenly palace in Tagi no Kohama (present-day {{ill|Izumo|ja|出雲市|12=draft}}), Kushiyatama, the grandson of the water deities Hayakitsuhiko and Hayakitsuhime, is appointed as the imperial chef. He transforms into a cormorant, gathers clay from the sea floor to create sacred vessels, and produces fire to prepare divine offerings. This act symbolizes his role as the ancestral deity of cuisine.
== Enshrined Shrines == * Mikado-nushi-hiko Shrine ({{ill|Nanao|ja|七尾市|12=draft}}, Ishikawa Prefecture) * Hida Takatsue Shrine ({{ill|Gero|ja|下呂市|12=draft}}, Gifu Prefecture) * Kiyahatama Shrine ({{ill|Tomioka|ja|富岡市|12=draft}}, Gunma Prefecture) * {{ill|Wadatsumi Shrine|ja|和田津見神社|12=draft}} ({{ill|Matsue|ja|松江市|12=draft}}, Shimane Prefecture) * {{ill|Minato Shrine (Izumo-taisha)|ja|湊社|12=draft}} ({{ill|Izumo|ja|出雲市|12=draft}}, Shimane Prefecture) * Kashima Shrine (Zōfu Shrine) (Izumo, Shimane Prefecture) * {{ill|Homori Shrine|ja|火守神社|12=draft}} (Izumo, Shimane Prefecture) * Kushiyatama Shrine ({{ill|Minabe|ja|みなべ町|12=draft}}, Wakayama Prefecture)
== References == {{Reflist}}
== Related Pages == * {{ill|Iwakamu Tsukari|ja|磐鹿六鴈|12=draft}} – Ancestral deity of cuisine like Kushiyatama.
