'''Kushiyatama''' (櫛八玉神), also known as Kiyahatama no Kami, is a deity appearing in [[:en:Japanese mythology|Japanese mythology]].
== Overview == Kushiyatama appears in the [[:en:Kojiki|Kojiki]] during the episode of the [[:en:Kuni-yuzuri|Transfer of the Land]]. He is considered the ancestor of the Bekke clan.
== Depiction == === In the Kojiki === After {{ill|Takeminakata|ja|建御名方神|1=Takeminakata|2=ja|3=タケミナカタ|lt=Takeminakata|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Takeminakata|qq=}} surrenders to {{ill|Takemikazuchi|ja|建御雷神|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Takemikazuchi|qq=}}, Takemikazuchi asks {{ill|Ōkuninushi|ja|大国主神|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōkuninushi|qq=}} about his loyalty. Ōkuninushi agrees to submit the land of Ashihara-no-Nakatsukuni if a grand palace is built for him, akin to the residence of the heavenly gods.
During the construction of the heavenly palace in Tagi no Kohama (present-day [[:en:Izumo, Shimane|Izumo]]), Kushiyatama, the grandson of the water deities Hayakitsuhiko and Hayakitsuhime, is appointed as the imperial chef. He transforms into a cormorant, gathers clay from the sea floor to create sacred vessels, and produces fire to prepare divine offerings. This act symbolizes his role as the ancestral deity of cuisine.
== Enshrined Shrines == * Mikado-nushi-hiko Shrine ([[:en:Nanao, Ishikawa|Nanao]], Ishikawa Prefecture) * Hida Takatsue Shrine ([[:en:Gero, Gifu|Gero]], Gifu Prefecture) * Kiyahatama Shrine ([[:en:Tomioka, Gunma|Tomioka]], Gunma Prefecture) * {{ill|Wadatsumi Shrine|ja|和田津見神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Wadatsumi Shrine|qq=}} ([[:en:Matsue|Matsue]], Shimane Prefecture) * {{ill|Minato Shrine (Izumo-taisha)|ja|湊社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Minato Shrine (Izumo-taisha)|qq=}} ([[:en:Izumo, Shimane|Izumo]], Shimane Prefecture) * Kashima Shrine (Zōfu Shrine) (Izumo, Shimane Prefecture) * {{ill|Homori Shrine|ja|火守神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Homori Shrine|qq=}} (Izumo, Shimane Prefecture) * Kushiyatama Shrine ([[:en:Minabe, Wakayama|Minabe]], Wakayama Prefecture)
